N:firebase-cli
D:[firebase-cli] Install, configure, and operate Firebase CLI for all Firebase services. Covers deploy, emulators, hosting preview channels, auth import/export, app distribution, extensions, app hosting, CI/CD. Installation: npm install -g firebase-tools.
G:firebase firebase-cli firebase-tools deploy hosting functions firestore database emulators auth remote-config app-distribution extensions apphosting ci-cd service-account preview-channel

U[9]:
  Deploy Firebase Hosting, Cloud Functions, Firestore rules/indexes, Realtime Database rules
  Set up a new Firebase project with firebase init
  Run the Firebase Emulator Suite locally for development and testing
  Manage preview/staging channels for Hosting before production deploy
  Import or export Firebase Authentication users in bulk
  Distribute app builds to testers via App Distribution
  Manage Firebase Extensions (install, configure, update, uninstall)
  Deploy Next.js / Angular apps via Firebase App Hosting
  Use Firebase CLI in CI/CD pipelines with service account credentials

S[5]{n,action,details}:
  1,Install,npm install -g firebase-tools OR curl -sL firebase.tools | bash (standalone binary)
  2,Auth,firebase login (browser OAuth) OR export GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/key.json for CI
  3,Init,firebase init (interactive: creates firebase.json and .firebaserc with project aliases)
  4,Deploy,firebase deploy OR firebase deploy --only hosting,functions (scope with --only in prod)
  5,Emulate,firebase emulators:start --import ./emulator-data --export-on-exit

R[8]:
  Use service accounts for CI/CD: set GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS instead of deprecated --token
  Always scope deploys with --only in production — never blindly deploy everything
  Run emulators:start locally before deploying; use --import/--export-on-exit for persistence
  Use hosting:channel:deploy for staging previews before firebase deploy --only hosting
  For Cloud Functions 2nd gen use functions:secrets:set (Secret Manager) not deprecated functions:config:set
  Always add --non-interactive in automated scripts to avoid hanging on prompts
  Commit .firebaserc (project aliases) but gitignore service account key files
  Run failing commands with --debug flag for verbose diagnostic output

E[6]{type,command}:
  Deploy all,firebase deploy
  Deploy scoped,firebase deploy --only hosting,functions
  Emulators with persistence,firebase emulators:start --import ./emulator-data --export-on-exit
  Preview channel,firebase hosting:channel:create staging --expires 7d && firebase hosting:channel:deploy staging
  Import auth users,firebase auth:import users.json --hash-algo=BCRYPT
  Distribute build,firebase appdistribution:distribute app.apk --app APP_ID --groups qa-team
